   <!-- SCREEN 4: ABOUT-->
  <section id="about">
    <div class="about-row">
      <div class="about-img">
        <img src="participants.jpeg" alt="Campus event" />
      </div>
      <div class="about-text">
        <h2>What is Eventure?</h2>
        <p>Eventure is a purpose-built desktop application that empowers student leaders to plan, manage, and monitor campus events from a single, unified interface.</p>
        <p>The system consolidates participant registration, capacity tracking, and attendance recording into one streamlined workflow — eliminating the need for disconnected spreadsheets, paper lists, or group chats.</p>
        <p>Designed with the university ecosystem in mind, Eventure gives student organizations the same level of operational control that professional event managers rely on — adapted for the campus environment.</p>
        <p>From creating a new event to generating post-event reports, every step is handled within Eventure, giving organizers full visibility and control throughout the entire event lifecycle.</p>
      </div>
    </div>




    <div class="about-row">
      <div class="about-text">
        <h2>Why Eventure matters</h2>
        <p>Campus events are essential to student life — but managing them is often a disorganized mess. Student organizations typically rely on scattered tools that aren't designed for the complexity of event coordination.</p>
        <p>Eventure was born from that frustration. It solves the real problems student leaders face: overcrowded venues, inaccurate headcounts, lost registration data, and last-minute scrambles to track who showed up.</p>
        <p>By centralizing everything — from initial event setup to real-time capacity monitoring — Eventure reduces the administrative burden on organizers and ensures participants have a smoother, more organized experience.</p>
        <p>Ultimately, Eventure matters because better-organized events mean better experiences for everyone on campus. It raises the standard of what student-led events can look like.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-img">
        <img src="Created Event.jpeg" alt="Eventure dashboard" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


